From 09f409e51566e9660178ec75c89ffe394f09e2ba Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:28:13 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 0/4] usb: typec: qcom-pmic: add PMI8998 port handler
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add PMI8998 USB Type-C support to the qcom-pmic TCPM driver by
introducing a sibling port handler alongside the existing PM8150B /
PMI632 code path.

PMI8998's Type-C controller block at SPMI offset 0x1300 has a
different register layout from PM8150B: different STATUS_4 bit
positions, hardware-managed CC debounce, and a single rollup IRQ
instead of separate CC and VBUS IRQs. PMI8998 also leaves the FSM in
micro-USB mode out of reset and needs a four-write/three-delay
bring-up dance before CC sensing starts. The PDPHY block at 0x1700
is byte-identical to PM8150B and is reused via the existing
pm8150b_pdphy_res.

Patch 1 lifts the port-handler probe behind a per-resource function
pointer so a future PMI8998 sibling can plug in next to pm8150b
without touching the dispatcher.

Patch 2 adds the PMI8998 port handler itself (one new file under
drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/qcom/). The change in size from v1 is
deliberate: rather than duplicating the entire port machinery, the
new file only implements the seven tcpc_dev callbacks and the
single-rollup ISR that are PMI8998-specific.

Patches 3-4 add the SoC-level DT nodes (in pmi8998.dtsi, disabled by
default) and enable Type-C on the OnePlus 6 / 6T common DT. The
boards advertise dual power and data roles, a single 5V/1.5A source
PDO and a single 5V/3A sink PDO, and a sink-vdos / sink-vdos-v1
identity that lets PD3.0 partners ACK Discover_Identity without
falling into a SOFT_RESET loop.

Hardware validation:
  - Xiaomi Mi 8 (dipper): end-to-end sink + host + role-swap + DRP
    dock + PD partner identity ACK; see the dipper port series
    sdm845-xiaomi-dipper.dts for the per-device DT.

OnePlus 6 / 6T DT enablement is included but not yet hardware-tested
in this repository snapshot.

Base: Mobian linux-6.12-sdm845 6.12.91-1. The series is otherwise
self-contained inside drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/qcom/ and a few DT
files; it does not depend on the dipper port series, only on a
recent enough drivers/usb/typec/tcpm/qcom/ baseline.

Max Furman (4):
  usb: typec: qcom-pmic: dispatch port backend via resource table
  usb: typec: qcom-pmic: add PMI8998 port handler
  arm64: dts: qcom: pmi8998: add Type-C and VBUS regulator nodes
  arm64: dts: qcom: sdm845-oneplus-common: enable Type-C

